task.summary: Default task

Replaced screen coordinates for the opening with the keys of the objects for the opening. Then it should be pretty simple to find the vector to the "objects" which match at a certain Y. The vectors are stored as [4:5]. Just choose the smallest angle, and that's the angle of the opening (A). the distances are (b) and (c), so, just need to calculate for (a)

There is a width estimation and it seems PRETTY accurate. But it does not correspond to the .blend file. The blend file says the two walls are 8m apart. The camera says they're 47-48cm apart... BUT in the simulator, it's near the width of the agent who just barely hits the wall (agent's width with arms down is 44cm). Suggests its CLOSE! I need to add a representation to the buffer if an opening is found. I need to add maybe 20% error on the width estimation to account for the perceptual error.
I think the vision system might be passable.
When up close, it doesn't work. Make sure that when you fint a new object, step INSIDE, then take depth. When at the edge of an object, step BACK, then take depth.

This also makes it update as it is supposed to. If the framerate drops though, the program will likely crash (hang). Still need a fix for slow frame rates.
